import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='distance', y='count', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axvline(avg_distance, color='red', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['airport'] = data['airport'].str.upper()
    airport_count = data.groupby('airport')['count'].sum().reset_index().sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    top_airports = airport_count.head(10)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='airport', y='count', data=top_airports, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?')
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    for i, v in enumerate(top_airports['count']):
        plt.text(i, v, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom', fontweight='bold')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    route_count = data.groupby('route').count().reset_index()
    route_count = route_count[['route', 'count']]
    route_count = route_count.sort_values('count', ascending=False)
    route_count = route_count.head(10)
    plt.pie(route_count['count'], labels=route_count['route'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight routes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
